FBIS4-19000 "drweu071__a94007" FBIS-WEU-94-071-A Daily Report 13 April 1994 ANNEX Germany Butrus-Ghali Arrives in Bonn for Talks With Kohl Butrus-Ghali Arrives in Bonn for Talks With Kohl AU1204151894 Hamburg DPA in German 1412 GMT 12 Apr 94--FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY AU1204151894 Hamburg DPA German BFN [Text] Bonn (DPA) -- UN Secretary General Butrus-Ghali arrived for an official visit to Bonn on Tuesday [12 April] following an invitation by Federal Chancellor Helmut Kohl. In his talks, which started with a meeting with Foreign Minister Klaus Kinkel and are scheduled to continue on Wednesday in a meeting with Federal Chancellor Helmut Kohl, the UN secretary general intends to encourage Germany's participation in a permanent UN reaction force. The Germans have announced that they were seeking closer cooperation with and within the United Nations, including a seat on the Security Council, and the transfer of UN organizations to Bonn. Butrus-Ghali will also meet members of parliament before his departure scheduled for Wednesday afternoon.
